ZH: 我今天需要割草。
EN: I need to mow the lawn today.

ZH: 周末是割草的好时机。
EN: The weekend is a good time for mowing the lawn.

ZH: 他每个星期割草两次。
EN: He mows the lawn twice a week.

ZH: 我已经割草完了，现在可以休息了。
EN: I have finished mowing the lawn, now I can rest.

ZH: 割草是个累人的工作。
EN: Mowing the lawn is a tiring job.

ZH: 割草机是我最喜欢的工具之一。
EN: The lawnmower is one of my favorite tools.

ZH: 每个月切割一次草坪可以保持草坪的整洁。
EN: Mowing the lawn once a month can keep it tidy.

ZH: 天气炎热，我们要割草时得注意保护好皮肤。
EN: It's hot, so we need to protect our skin when mowing.

ZH: 我喜欢割草的声音，觉得很放松。
EN: I like the sound of mowing the lawn, it's relaxing.

ZH: 割草时不小心弄脏了鞋子。
EN: I accidentally got my shoes dirty while mowing.

ZH: 割草后，草坪看起来整齐多了。
EN: After mowing the lawn, it looks much neater.

ZH: 在我们家，割草是孩子的责任之一。
EN: In our family, mowing the lawn is one of the children's responsibilities.

ZH: 这台割草机能够自动回收割下的草渣。
EN: This lawnmower can automatically collect the cut grass.

ZH: 我将邀请几个朋友一起割草。
EN: I will invite a few friends to mow the lawn together.

ZH: 割草的时候，我喜欢穿着舒适的运动服。
EN: I like wearing comfortable sportswear while mowing the lawn.

ZH: 跳跃起来割草真是一种享受。
EN: Jumping up and down while mowing the lawn is a real pleasure.

ZH: 我给割草那片区域画了一条界线。
EN: I drew a line to mark the area I need to mow.

ZH: 割草期间，我不小心踩到了一只蚂蚁。
EN: I accidentally stepped on an ant while mowing the lawn.

ZH: 我家后院的的草已经长得很高了，该割草了。
EN: The grass in my backyard has grown very tall, it's time to mow.

ZH: 割草前，我会先检查割草机是否工作正常。
EN: Before mowing the lawn, I will check if the lawnmower is working properly.
